<br>
I don't know about your server, but, on Cazic, most post 50 rogues get scooped up by the Uber guilds.  It's very common for smaller guilds (even with many post 50 characters) to not have any post 50 rogues.  My guild is just like that.  We have plenty of firepower in the over 50 world, but our highest level rogue is 35ish.  This makes raids to places like Howling Stones very difficult and often it prevents us from getting past the first wing.  We've spent 5 hours in the wing and never even saw the key mob for the next level.  It's nearly impossible for my guild to help its druid and ranger population to get Jade Reavers since we have no rogue high enough to pick the lock.<br>
<br>
I guess you can see where this is going.  I would love to see wizards get some sort of &quot;knock&quot; spell.  It would make wizards a little more usefull at high levels (where most of these locks are).  It would also solve problems like the lack of rogues for guilds like mine.<br>
<br>
Ok, the motivation may be a bit selfish.  I also realize that this would piss off a lot of rogues, but, I really do believe it to be a problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 226<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/10/01 1:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: One way to make Wizards a little more welcome</span><hr size=1> Although I don't think it would fly in the eyes of VI, I do like the idea and will support it by responding.<br>
